<P>
CAMACHO IS WINNER OVER LAWLOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hector Camacho outpointed Pat Lawlor in a 10-round welterweight bout Tuesday 
night at Casino Magic. 
</P>
<P>
 Fighting at 153 pounds, the 32-year-old Camacho (47-3) won every round on two 
of the judges' cards and lost only one round on the other final card. 
</P>
<P>
 Camacho, a three-time world champion returning from a three-month layoff, 
settled into a rhythm early, knocking Lawlor down in the first round with a 
straight left to the nose. 
</P>
<P>
 Lawlor is 20-5. 
</P>
