<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Charles Grantham, head of the NBA players' union, says he would not be 
surprised if the league staged a lockout because of the salary cap. He said 
players would be prepared to stage "alternative" games. 
</P>
<P>
 There is no current labor contract in the NBA, and owners reportedly are 
considering a lockout if none is reached by Thanksgiving. College Basketball 
</P>
<P>
 Coastal Carolina's athletic program was put on four years' probation by the 
NCAA for violations in its men's basketball program that included academic 
fraud. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chanticleers also were banned from postseason play for a season, won't be 
allowed on television this season and will have fewer basketball scholarships 
the next three seasons. 
