<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; SECOND-RANKED SAN CLEMENTE SHUTS DOWN NO. 1 CORONA DEL MAR IN WATER 
POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The San Clemente water polo team held Corona del Mar to four goals in the 
final three quarters and defeated the top-ranked Sea Kings, 13-10, Tuesday at 
Corona del Mar High. 
</P>
<P>
 The second-ranked Tritons (6-1), who lost to the Sea Kings, 11-7, in the 
semifinals of the South Coast tournament Saturday, never trailed Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 After a fast-paced first quarter that ended in a 6-6 tie, the Sea Kings failed 
to score on 10 consecutive possessions and San Clemente led 7-6 at the half. 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar (5-2) increased its defensive effort in the third quarter and 
Adrian Strelzow's goal ended the Sea Kings' scoring drought and cut the Triton 
lead to one goal with 5 minutes 40 seconds left in the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 But Jordan Hewko scored his fifth goal of the game and Andy Bailey added 
another goal a minute later to increase the Tritons' lead to three. 
</P>
<P>
 A penalty-shot goal by Neil Hueston made it 10-8 at the end of three quarters, 
but the Tritons started the fourth with a man-advantage goal by Colin 
Shaughnessy. 
</P>
<P>
 Thad Buzolich cut the lead to 11-9 with 3:31 remaining, but that's as close as 
the Sea Kings would come as Andy Bailey and Jim Farley scored late in the game 
to secure the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Gabe Gardner had 10 saves, including five in the fourth quarter, for the 
Tritons. 
</P>
<P>
 Hueston had five goals and Buzolich added three to lead the Sea Kings. DAN 
ARRITT 
</P>
</TEXT>
