<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; LAGUNA BEACH ROLLS BY NEWPORT HARBOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laguna Beach has Orange County bragging rights, for now, after the top-ranked 
Artists' defeated No. 2 Newport Harbor, 11-7, in girls' tennis Tuesday at 
Newport Harbor High School. 
</P>
<P>
 The Artists, ranked No. 1 in Division II, rolled over the Sailors in the first 
round, taking a 5-1 lead.Laguna Beach (6-1) swept its doubles in the round and 
suffered its only loss when Sarah Hawkins defeated Lindsay Weiss, 6-0, in 
singles. 
</P>
<P>
 "The doubles were huge," Artist Coach Bob Walton said. "The first round was 
the key. There was no way I thought we'd sweep." 
</P>
<P>
 Aiming for their third consecutive Southern Section Division II title, the 
Artists looked strong in doubles and singles. 
</P>
<P>
 Amanda Hastings-Phillips led the way, sweeping her first two singles sets, 
6-0, 6-1, before scoring a 6-4 victory over Hawkins. A senior, Hawkins usually 
plays in the No. 1 spot for Newport Harbor (2-1), but moved to the No. 3 
position so she could get some extra warm-up time. She won her other set 6-1. 
</P>
<P>
 At No. 1 doubles, Sarah Cohen and Vanessa Zajfen took two of three, 6-4, 2-6, 
6-1, losing to the the Sailors' sophomore team of Katie Canright and Emily 
Barker. 
</P>
<P>
 Zajfen, disappointed by her play, cracked the books between sets. After Zajfen 
got some homework done, she and Cohen defeated Katie Hawkins and Brooke Taylor, 
6-1. 
</P>
<P>
 After the match Walton was all smiles. "I'm glad we aren't Division I," he 
said. "Now we can go back and play Division II." MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</TEXT>
