<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In other nonleague girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa 12, Westminster 6 -- Uyen Nguyen and Lananh Do swept their sets, 
6-4, 6-1, 6-2, for Costa Mesa (4-4). 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro 14, Capistrano Valley 4 -- Michelle Shomaker, Shelly Vernick and 
Amanda Hoskins won the nine singles sets for host El Toro (4-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 12, San Clemente 6 -- Sarah Denson swept at No. 1 singles, 6-2, 6-0, 
6-1, to lead visiting Irvine (6-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In Century League tennis: 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 17, Orange 1 -- Shannon Wilkens and Kim Westermann swept their singles 
sets and Candi Ramos and Sharmi Das swept their doubles sets for Canyon (8-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park 11, El Modena 7 -- Jill Riley and Shawna Lerer swept at No. 1 
doubles, 6-1, 6-2, 6-0, to lead visiting Villa Park (5-1, 1-0). Brandi 
Freudenberg swept at No. 1 singles, 6-1, 6-0, 6-0, for El Modena. 
</P>
<P>
 In Empire League tennis: 
</P>
<P>
