<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: CATFISH AND RACCOON ARE ACTIVE AT LAKE PIRU 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It's not often that all the catfish in a lake decide to feed at once.But it 
seems to have happened at Lake Piru. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have no idea why, but we've had over 300 pounds of catfish caught since 
Friday," said Art Caldara, manager of the Ventura County reservoir. 
</P>
<P>
 Ennis Choyce of Altadena had one of the most impressive stringers, catching 
seven catfish totaling 92 pounds 8 ounces. But everyone seems to be getting 
into the act. 
</P>
<P>
 Caldara said a seven-pounder he had soaking on a string was attacked and eaten 
by a raccoon. 
</P>
<P>
 "He got it at the dock and just tore that thing apart," Caldara said. "He got 
my dinner." 
</P>
</TEXT>
