<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; CYPRESS GETS LOOSE, BEATS OCC IN WOMEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a frustrating first half, Cypress scored three goals in the second half 
and went on to a 3-0 victory over Orange Coast in an Orange Empire Conference 
women's soccer game Tuesday at OCC. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress, which has won 26 consecutive conference games, missed on three easy 
chances in the first half. But the Chargers finally scored five minutes into 
the second half when Pam Prine headed in a corner kick by Tracy Van Herk. 
Christine Rowe scored on a penalty kick in the 76th minute and then Traci Osman 
scored just before the end of the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress (4-0, 2-0) dominated play the entire game, outshooting OCC, 22-2. 
Orange Coast is 4-2, 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In another women's conference soccer game: 
</P>
<P>
