COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: DANA POINT, LAGUNA BEACH; INPUT SOUGHT ON WATER DISTRICT 
CONSOLIDATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The South Coast Water District will have a special meeting Saturday to discuss 
options on how to best consolidate water and sewer agencies that serve Dana 
Point. 
</P>
<P>
 The public is invited to attend the 9 a.m. meeting in the administrative 
offices of the South Coast Water District, 31592 West St., Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 The water district's consolidation committee will present three alternatives. 
</P>
<P>
 The Local Agency Formation Commission has suggested that a single agency 
provide water and sewer service to the city of Dana Point.JEFF BEAN 
