<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Andrea Bill 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback, Sophomore 
</P>
<P>
 Volleyball/Outside hitter 
</P>
<P>
 Bill had a solid season for Saddleback last season, helping the Gauchos to the 
playoffs.But during the summer, she considered transferring to UC Santa Barbara 
to continue her discus career. She was one of the top throwers in the state as 
a senior at University High, winning a Southern Section title. She changed her 
mind and returned to Saddleback. She had 17 kills in a four-game victory over 
El Camino and 10 in a sweep of Citrus. Soccer 
</P>
<P>
 Shannon Cunningham 
</P>
<P>
 * Irvine Valley, sophomore. Had two goals in a 3-1 victory over Fullerton and 
another in a 4-2 loss to Palomar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Profile 
