<P>
ATHLETE OF THE WEEK / GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Darcie Frazier 
</P>
<P>
 SCHOOL: L.A. Baptist 
</P>
<P>
 SPORT: Volleyball 
</P>
<P>
 YEAR: Senior 
</P>
<P>
 SEASON AT A GLANCE: Frazier, a 5-foot-9 outside hitter, has helped L.A. 
Baptist to a 5-0 record. Frazier and setter Tunde Hrotko are the only returning 
starters from a team that lost in the 1993 Southern Section Division V 
quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
 WEEK AT A GLANCE: Frazier had 27 kills over two matches as L.A. Baptist 
defeated Canyon and previously unbeaten La Canada. In the Santa Paula 
tournament over the weekend, Frazier had 79 kills and was named tournament most 
valuable player. The Knights won all 11 games, including a 15-13 victory over 
St. Bonaventure in the final. "She really is our best offensive weapon and our 
go-to person," Coach Sue Newcomb said. "Darcie and Tunde have helped us to more 
success than we thought we'd have." 
</P>
