HEAVY RAINS CAUSE FLOODING IN GUATEMALA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities evacuated three villages in central Guatemala after two 
rain-swollen rivers burst their banks. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 600 people were rescued from villages in the province of Alta 
Verapaz after 72 hours of torrential rains, government officials said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 No deaths were reported, but crops and homes were damaged. 
</P>
