</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A one-month-old boy was found safe in Las Vegas on Tuesday after being 
kidnaped from an El Monte motel more than a week ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Otto Ivan Guillermo was abducted from Caesar's Motel on Garvey Avenue by a 
woman who befriended his mother, Christina Macias, 28, and then disappeared 
with the infant, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The alleged kidnaper, who police believe is named Stacey Tomlinson, was 
arrested in Las Vegas on Tuesday morning after El Monte police received a phone 
call from a truck driver who said he had bought the woman a plane ticket to Las 
Vegas. The trucker alerted authorities after hearing radio reports about the 
kidnaping, police said. 
