 Reader Vern Fagin of Studio City says his son Matt, 8, suffers from being the 
progeny of two attorneys. Matt's class assignment was to say what people need 
besides shelter to survive. 
</P>
<P>
 So he explained to his class: "You need food, water, clothing, a job, good 
health . . . and a good lawyer."  
