<HEADLINE>
<P>
FATHER GETS 1-YEAR SENTENCE IN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 42-year-old father was sentenced to one year in jail Tuesday because his 
5-year-old son was injured in a traffic accident while not wearing a seat belt, 
according to the Los Angeles city attorney's office. 
</P>
<P>
 Mitchell Gluckman of Canoga Park pleaded no contest to one count each of child 
endangerment, hit-and-run driving and possession of a fraudulently obtained 
driver's license, according to City Atty.James Hahn. 
</P>
<P>
 In June, Gluckman was driving with his son, who was not wearing a seat belt, 
on Saticoy Street near Reseda Boulevard. Gluckman's car struck a stationary car 
at 35 m.p.h. and the boy's face hit the windshield and cracked the glass, the 
statement read. 
</P>
<P>
 Gluckman showed the driver of the other car a phony driver's license bearing 
the name of his young son before leaving the scene of the accident, according 
to the statement. JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
