<TEXT>
<P>
 Kmart Hires Outsider to Run Cost Cutting: The retailer said it hired a new 
executive vice president to oversee its cost-cutting program, further 
demonstrating its growing willingness to hire key executives from outside its 
ranks.Kmart Corp. named Marvin Rich, executive vice president of Wellpoint 
Health Networks Inc., to the new post. He will report directly to Chairman 
Joseph Antonini. In making the announcement, the country's second-biggest 
retailer, long known for hiring and promoting from within, made a point of 
noting its outside hires in its news release. 
</P>
