<HEADLINE>
<P>
NORTHWEST TRIGGERS ANOTHER AIR FARE BATTLE; AIRLINES: RIVALS SAY THEY'LL MATCH 
THE CARRIER'S 2-FOR-1 OFFER. THE OFFER PUTS THE PRICE OF AN L.A.-NEW YORK ROUND 
TRIP FOR TWO AT $643. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS WOODYARD, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In the latest in a string of fall discounts, Northwest Airlines hatched a 
domestic 2-for-1 air fare sale Tuesday that cuts the price of a round-trip 
flight from Los Angeles to Chicago to $569 for two. The deal was matched by 
many major carriers. 
</P>
<P>
 The promotion, offering discounts of 50% for two people traveling together, 
are in line with a series of previous reductions this fall that have routinely 
cut the price of a round-trip ticket to the East to less than $400. Like the 
previous sales, the Northwest offer requires 14-day advance purchase and travel 
between Oct. 11 and Feb. 15. 
</P>
<P>
 The Northwest deal would let two people fly from Los Angeles to Miami for $628 
and to New York for $643.  
</P>
<P>
 A round trip for two from Orange County's John Wayne Airport to Detroit would 
be $575. Tickets must be purchased by Friday, and lesser discounts are 
available for international travel. 
</P>
<P>
 The deal is not available during popular travel days near the Thanksgiving and 
Christmas holidays. 
</P>
<P>
 Major airlines -- including American, USAir, Delta, Continental and America 
West -- said they would match the Northwest offer on routes in which the 
carriers compete. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, America West announced a new phase of its discounting with 
reductions of up to 52% to selected cities.  
</P>
<P>
 Travel agents said the newest discounts appear to be a response to consumers' 
expectations of lower prices. 
</P>
<P>
 "There are so many of these popping up one right after another," said Dianne 
LaPorte, vice president at World Travel in Santa Ana. "They are becoming the 
norm rather than the exception." 
</P>
</TEXT>
