NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A folk concert sponsored by the Orange Coast Unitarian Universalist Church in 
Costa Mesa Saturday raised $1,300 for the AIDS Team Ministry, according to 
spokesperson Dorothy White. The ministry, operated by the church and by the 
Metropolitan Community Church, also in Costa Mesa, provides meals to homebound 
people with AIDS and is the only such program in Orange County; it prepares and 
delivers 360 meals per month. Performers at the concert included Guy Richard, 
Tom Sanders, Barbara McGraw and Canton and Rhiannon Clannach. 
</P>
